name: Le Petit Trianon Theatre
dealTitle: Classical Guitarist David Leisner at South Bay Guitar Society
dealinfo: The South Bay Guitar Society exists to bring together guitarists of all experience levels and walks of life to share in the joy of music. For this performance, the SBGS welcomes classical guitarist David Leisner to San Jose's Trianon Theatre. An acclaimed performer, teacher and composer, Leisner has written nearly 50 original compositions for solo guitar, chamber ensembles and orchestras. An avid music researcher, Liesner is known for performing little- played works that have been lost to time, such as the compositions of Johann Kaspar Mertz.

name: The Dancing Cat
dealTitle: COMP  for $5.00  - The Cats Are Holding a Social Hour at The Dancing Cat, and You're Invited
dealinfo: This is your chance to, quite literally, hang out with the coolest cats in town. San Jose's The Dancing Cat is a creative space for people, and sometimes adoptable cats are able to get in on the human interaction. The space provides a living room-like ambiance where anywhere between seven and 11 lucky cats can wander and play in a cage-free environment. Visitors go there to meet friends, read, study or simply lounge with adoptable cats under a ceiling of colorful paper lanterns. Whether you're looking to adopt or just like to soak up the cool cat vibe and maybe scratch behind a few furry ears, this is one hour of your time that won't be wasted.

name: SJSU University Theatre
dealTitle: A Girl Battles Evil Cheerleaders and Randy Ogres in Action Comedy "She Kills Monsters"
dealinfo: After losing her sister, Agnes Evans departs her childhood home, but soon becomes enthralled with her late sister's Dungeons and Dragons notebook. Her journey coincides with an action-packed adventure through an imaginary world as she battles evil cheerleaders, randy ogres and homicidal faeries in the action-filled comedy "She Kills Monsters". A 2012 GLAAD Award nominee, the play explores the wounds of loss and adolescence. Reality, fantasy and '90s pop culture collide in this empowering story about embracing your inner badass (and geek) at the SJSU Theatre in San Jose.

name: Student Union Theater, San Jose State University
dealTitle: Acclaimed Author Francisco Jimenez in Conversation With Lalo Alcaraz
dealinfo: Francisco Jimenez's "The Circuit: Stories From The Life Of A Migrant Child" is a powerful series of interlinked stories about the author's upbringing as a migrant farmworker. The poignant stories are loaded with images of abject poverty, yet full of hope and dignity. Jimenez grew up to become a prominent author and intellectual, and he's now set to receive the prestigious John Steinbeck Award, which honors artists and activists for social engagement. Past recipients have included Bruce Springsteen, Garrison Keillor, Ken Burns and Joan Baez. Be there when Jimenez accepts his Steinbeck Award and joins cartoonist-intellectual Lalo Alcaraz in conversation at the Student Union Theater at San Jose State University.

name: Gigantour featuring Megadeth with Motörhead, Volbeat, and Lacuna Coil
dealTitle: sjDANCEco Season Opener: Modern Dance Set to Live Music
dealinfo: San Jose's sjDANCEco opens its season with a dazzling night of dance at California Theatre, featuring the premiere of "Goddesses and...", a choreographic collaboration between sjDANCEco, Abhinaya Dance Company and Karen Gabay, longtime Ballet San Jose principal dancer. Also on the program is a revival of artistic director Maria Basile's "The River", along with the company premieres of Dominic Duong's "Written in Calligraphy: From Heaven to Earth" and Gabriel Mata's award-nominated "Falling". The show is accompanied by live music from the San Jose Chamber Orchestra, under the baton of conductor Barbara D. Turner. Come early for a pre-performance discussion with artistic director Gary Masters.

name: Various San Jose Locations-Pubcrawls.com
dealTitle: Get Your Drink on With PubCrawls.com
dealinfo: Whatever your favorite imbibing holiday happens to be -- St. Patrick's Day, Cinco de Mayo, Halloween, Christmas, New Year's Eve or all of the above -- a pub crawl is the perfect way to celebrate. There's no figuring out which of Houston's many bars have the best drink specials, since all that pesky planning and prep work has been done for you. All you have to do is show up, claim your map of participating clubs (all within walking distance), and raise a glass or three with old friends and those you meet along the way. The PubCrawls.com gang has previously broken the world record for largest bar-hop ever hosted, and is always on the hunt to reclaim the title.

name: San Jose Improv
dealTitle: COMP  for $25.00 - Comedian-Actor John Witherspoon at the San Jose Improv
dealinfo: "Co-ordinate" a date to see John Witherspoon, one of the nation's top stand-up headliners, who's known for hilarious catchphrases like "Bang! Bang! Bang! Bang!" He's also played eccentric, short-tempered dads in the  Friday  series of films and TV's  The Wayans Bros.  and  The Boondocks , and appeared in music videos alongside Jay-Z and Sugar Ray. He's made more than a dozen appearances on the  Late Show with David Letterman , and his TV credits range from  The Richard Pryor Show  in 1977 to  Hill Street Blues ,  The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air ,  L. A. Law  and  The Tracy Morgan Show. Now he comes to play the world famous San Jose Improv.

name: Camera 12 Downtown
dealTitle: $10.00 for $18.00 - Summer Movie Musical Sing-Alongs: Costumes, Contests & Fun for All
dealinfo: Relive all the magic and fun of seeing your favorite movie musicals on the big screen at the  Summer Sing-Along Series. Presented by The Retro Dome at Camera 12 Downtown in San Jose, this blast-to-the-past series lets you sing, dance and cheer along to a handpicked selection of cinematic crowdpleasers like  Grease ,  Annie ,  The Princess Bride ,  Hairspray ,  The Music Man , and  Aladdin. Everyone in attendance receives a fun pack of themed props, and each screening features on-screen lyrics, fun in-movie surprises and pre-show costume, trivia or singing contests. Costumes are strongly encouraged, so get creative!

name: Camera 12 Cinemas
dealTitle: Summer Movie Musical Sing-Alongs: Costumes, Contests & Fun for All
dealinfo: Relive all the magic and fun of seeing your favorite movie musicals on the big screen at the "Summer Sing-Along Series". Presented by The Retro Dome at Camera 12 Downtown in San Jose, this blast-to-the-past series lets you sing, dance and cheer along to a handpicked selection of cinematic crowdpleasers like "Raiders of the Lost Arc", "Oklahoma!", and "Grease: The Singalong Experience!". Everyone in attendance receives a fun pack of themed props, and each screening features on-screen lyrics, fun in-movie surprises and pre-show costume, trivia or singing contests. Costumes are strongly encouraged, so get creative!

name: Downtown Ice
dealTitle: Skate Under the Stars at San Jose's Downtown Ice Skating Rink
dealinfo: Who needs snow in the wintertime? Enjoy an evening of ice skating under the stars and palm trees at downtown San Jose's Circle of Palms Plaza amidst other South Bay seasonal attractions such as the traditional Christmas in the Park and Winter Wonderland. The South Bay's largest seasonal outdoor skating rink, produced by the San Jose Downtown Association, partners with Kristi Yamaguchi's Always Dream Foundation and routinely attracts more than 100,000 people each season. Your ticket includes admission to Downtown Ice's circular rink, plus skate rental.

name: Northside Theatre Co
dealTitle: High Stakes in Pulitzer Winner "The Gin Game"
dealinfo: In D.L. Coburn's sharp-witted dramedy, a game of cards between two lonely nursing-home residents turns into a battle royale with serious personal stakes. Weller and Fonsia strike up a friendly acquaintance as he teaches her to play gin rummy, revealing intimate details of their lives along the way. But as Fonsia wins hand after hand, Weller becomes frustrated, and their simple past-time becomes an all-out war, with shared secrets as weapons of mass emotional destruction. This Pulitzer Prize winner was revived on Broadway earlier this year with James Earl Jones and Cicely Tyson. It now comes to the Olinder Theatre and is presented by Northside Theatre Company.

name: Mosaic Restaurant
dealTitle: $34.00  for $49.00  - 78 Degrees' Whiskey & Scotch Tastings
dealinfo: The spirited NorCal spirits experts at 78 Degrees are set to introduce you to the latest trends in whiskey, scotch, bourbon and the fine art of mixology through a variety of themed tastings, from the Whiskey World Tour and a Scotch and Food Pairing to a make-your-own-cocktail class. At each entertaining event you'll not only learn how to properly observe, nose and taste each of five different samples, but you'll pick up some interesting history on distilleries and whiskeys across the globe, as well as learning the difference between single and double barrels and malts, so you can order a drink like a true pro. The VIP experience offers early entry with welcome hors d'oeuvres, prime seating and a special taste of a premium blend.

name: Montgomery Theater
dealTitle: Anthony Bourdain: Globetrotting Chef's Latest Live Show
dealinfo: Chef, raconteur and world traveler Anthony Bourdain is hitting the road for another of his legendary live tours. Bourdain's latest live show, entitled "The Hunger", serves up an all-new experience featuring an unyielding, brutally honest monologue reflecting on diverse cultural experiences, street food and his travels to lesser-known locations around the world, followed by a no-holds-barred question and answer session. Known for stirring the pot, this "enfant terrible" might say anything when given free reign to speak, so you don't want to miss it when he hits San Jose Center for the Performing Arts to get real with his fans. You may even get to ask him a question, so come prepared!

name: San Jose Center for the Performing Arts
dealTitle: $62.50  for $62.50  - "John Cleese & Eric Idle: Together Again At Last ... For The Very First Time"
dealinfo: Two of the living legends of comedy perform together again on stage at last (for the very first time). John Cleese and Eric Idle have been beloved by generations of comedy fans for their groundbreaking work with Monty Python. Don't miss this rare chance to see two certified comedy geniuses when they take the stage at the San Jose Center for the Performing Arts. The British icons will perform hilarious sit-down comedy, combing scripted and improvised bits with storytelling, musical numbers, exclusive footage, aquatic juggling and an extended audience Q&A. No two shows will be quite the same, thus ensuring that every audience feels like they're seeing  Together Again At Last . For The Very First Time , for the very first time.

name: The Stage
dealTitle: $21.00  for $42.00  - "The Wild Party": See the Steamy Prohibition-Era Musical
dealinfo: Queenie, a showgirl during the Jazz Age, has grown tired and resentful of her relationship with a clown named Burrs. To get back into the swing of things (and to get back at the violent Burrs), she decides to throw a party. As their friends start to tumble in and the booze flows freely, the evening turns increasingly dark and decadent until . a gun goes off. But who exactly has been shot? Tony-nominee Andrew Lippa ( The Addams Family ,  I Am Harvey Milk ) wrote the book, lyrics and pulse-racing music for this one-of-a-kind, award-winning show that captures the verve and violence of the Roaring '20s. Don't miss San Jose Stage Company's production of  The Wild Party .

name: City National Civic
dealTitle: $40.50 for $52.00 - NEEDTOBREATHE:  "Tour de Compadres" With Mat Kearney, John Mark McMillan & Welshly Arms
dealinfo: Grammy-nominated NEEDTOBREATHE hails from South Carolina, effortlessly weaving the musical traditions and faith of their upbringing in the Deep South into their own unique brand of rock. Made up of brothers Bear Rinehart (lead vocals, guitar) and Bo Rinehart (guitar, vocals), Seth Bolt (bass, vocals) and Josh Lovelace (keys, vocals), the band hit the ground running in 2005 with their first big record deal, and the ensuing years have seen five full studio albums, chart-topping cross-genre success, multiple headlining tours and numerous television appearances. Following on the heels of the band's critically acclaimed album  Rivers In the Wasteland , which debuted at No. 3 on the Billboard 200 in 2014,  Hard Love  drops in July and is the inspiration for the cross-country  Tour de Compadres  that kicks off in August. See them in concert, joined by special guests Mat Kearney, John Mark McMillan and Welshly Arms when they come through San Jose's City National Civic this September.

name: San Jose McEnery Convention Center
dealTitle: COMP  for $45.00  - Stars From "Arrow", "The Flash" and More at "Heroes & Villains Fan Fest"
dealinfo: Heroes & Villains Fan Fest  flies into the San Jose McEnery Convention Center with one super-powered goal in mind: to revolutionize the comic-con landscape. How will they do that? By giving you, the fans, the opportunity to personally meet your favorite celebrities -- from  Arrow's  Stephen Amell to the cast of  The Flash  -- as well as the chance to learn behind-the-scenes info on the TV shows you live for, straight from the creators and cast members. Plus, you're not just lining up, or sitting in an audience; you can participate in obstacles, try your hand at games of skill and maybe even gain a power or two. By the end of the two-day immersive  Heroes & Villains  experience, lucky fans will have posed for photo ops with stars like Karen Gillan and Michael Rooker ( Guardians of the Galaxy ) or  The Flash 's Robbie Amell, learned the latest details on their favorite sci-fi series, and put their own muscular or mental might to the test.

name: Various San Jose Venues - Mission Chamber Orchestra
dealTitle: Classics and New Works by the Mission Chamber Orchestra of San Jose
dealinfo: The Mission Chamber Orchestra of San Jose (MCOSJ) has delighted Silicon Valley audiences with its high-quality performances and innovative programming for two decades. And though they're equally adept at both classical and contemporary pieces, the ensemble is known for its world premieres of more than 20 new original works by some of the world's greatest composers. Music Director Emily Ray leads the 50-member orchestra, as well as up-and-coming soloists and professional guest artists and vocalists, through a four-concert season at several historic venues throughout San Jose, including the beautiful Trianon Theatre.

name: Under the Big White Top
dealTitle: "Odysseo": Cavalia's Theatrical Equine Extravaganza Gallops Into San Jose
dealinfo: Following extended sold-out engagements around the world, Cavalia is back with its latest equestrian and acrobatic extravaganza: "Odysseo". With a production double the size of the original, "Odysseo" combines equestrian and stage arts with high-tech theatrical effects at never-before-seen levels and leads you on a fabulous journey to discover some of the planet's most unforgettable landscapes. You'll be transported to a whole new level of beauty, grace and magic, this time featuring 70 magnificent horses and 45 artists from all over the globe. "Odysseo" is the world's largest touring production and has the largest touring tent on Earth, the biggest stage, the most breathtaking visual effects and the greatest number of horses at liberty. This is your chance to be amazed and enchanted when Cavalia's "Odysseo" gallops into downtown San Jose!

name: San Jose Arena Green East
dealTitle: $17.50 for $35.00 - Light Up the Night at The Lantern Run
dealinfo: In Asia, lantern festivals are lively outdoor parties lit by hundreds of glowing paper lanterns, which festivalgoers write their wishes on, set aflame and release into the air at the end of the night. East meets West at The Lantern Run, which combines the outdoor nighttime fun of a lantern festival with the runner's high of a 5K. Participants in this run through San Jose's scenic Arena Green East will receive a goody bag full of snacks, glow gear to wear during the run, and an LED lantern to write wishes on and release at the after party.

name: SAP Center at San Jose
dealTitle: "Ringling Bros. and Barnum & Bailey" Presents "Out Of This World"
dealinfo: Prepare to blast off on an intergalactic adventure for space-age family fun as the ultimate circus experience launches into the future with "Ringling Bros. and Barnum & Bailey" Presents "Out Of This World". Audiences will take the helm to join the Circus Space Fleet on a heroic quest of good versus evil that will let imaginations run wild with unexpected surprises and thrills at every turn. Through the lens of a magic telescope, "Out Of This World" transports your entire family on an unforgettable journey as the circus Star Seeker battles to bring the most spectacular and talented performers back to Earth after years in outer space. Children of all ages will be amazed by the cosmic voyage as you discover the wonders of gravity-defying acrobats, orbital aerialists, majestic animals, fearless daredevils and humorous clowns at the SAP Center at San Jose.

name: SAP Center at San Jose
dealTitle: $30.00 for $49.95 - Demi Lovato & Nick Jonas: "Future Now"
dealinfo: Two stars, one fantastic summer concert. Demi Lovato and Nick Jonas join forces this summer for their 2016 Honda Civic  Future Now  Tour, and it's making a stop at the SAP Center at San Jose. Lovato is a fearless singer-songwriter at the top of her game. She released her fifth studio album,  Confident , in 2015 with the hit singles "Cool for the Summer" and the album's title track. Since beginning her career as a child actor and releasing her first album in 2008, she's released four more albums, toured, served as a judge for two seasons of  The X Factor  and launched her own skincare and makeup lines. Also a child actor, Jonas rose to fame as one-third of the Jonas Brothers pop rock band. He struck out on his own in 2014, releasing his self-titled album featuring the hit singles "Chains" and "Jealous. " His latest single, "Levels," has already attracted over 12 million views on YouTube. See these longtime collaborators in concert as they sing their own hits, plus join voices for songs like the duet "Avalanche" from Jonas' album.

name: Anthony R. Soto Theatre
dealTitle: "The Little Mermaid": Disney Classic Takes You "Under the Sea"
dealinfo: A musical adaptation of one of Hans Christian Andersen's most beloved stories and the classic Disney movie, "The Little Mermaid" takes your whole family on a magical journey under and above the high seas at the Anthony R. Soto Theatre in San Jose. Ariel, an adventurous young mermaid, has a thing for disobeying the rules and following her heart. Her fascination with the human world often leads her to the sea surface, a zone that's designated as off limits by her father Triton, the sea king. One day while sneaking to the surface, Ariel witnesses a shipwreck and rescues Prince Eric, with whom she becomes instantly smitten. She defies her father, King Triton, and makes a deal with Ursula the sea witch to become human. But can she win over the prince -- and convince him she's the girl whose enchanting voice he's been seeking? With music by eight- time Academy Award winner Alan Menken, this Chrysalis Youth Theatre production of this beloved fairy tale will capture your heart with iconic songs like "Under the Sea," "Kiss the Girl" and "Part of Your World."

name: Grand Chapiteau at Taylor Street Bridge
dealTitle: "Cirque du Soleil: LUZIA": A Waking Dream of Mexico
dealinfo: Step right up into the Grand Chapiteau in San Jose and discover the surreal world of "LUZIA", where an imaginary Mexico springs to life to the soundtrack of brassy Mexican and Latin American sounds. Inspired by the cultural richness of Mexico, "Cirque du Soleil"'s new big-top show "LUZIA" features original music written for a live acoustic setting mixed with the electro-pop of Nortec Collective's Bostich + Fussible. Catch "LUZIA" -- a combination of the Spanish words "luz" (light) and "lluvia" (rain), two elements at the heart of the show -- on the San Jose stop of its world tour, which kicked off in Montreal in April 2016. Plus, you'll receive a souvenir and food and beverage item with each ticket purchased.

name: Mexican Heritage Plaza
dealTitle: "The Conference of the Birds": Perilous, Dance-Filled Journey Toward Understanding
dealinfo: Thirty artists representing 10 dance traditions spanning four continents join forces at Mexican Heritage Plaza for a movement-based adaptation of the vibrant, multi-sensory fable "The Conference of the Birds". Based on a legendary 12th-century Persian poem, it tells the allegorical story of a flock of birds, who set off on a treacherous quest to find the legendary phoenix- like creature that represents the Divine. With Hoopoe the wise one leading the way, they follow a painful but beautiful path toward realization of the Sufi idea of transcendent totality. First staged in 1971 with Helen Mirren in the lead role, "The Conference of the Birds" was written by Tony-winning director Peter Brook and acclaimed French novelist Jean-Claude Carriere, who based their script on real conversations with villagers living along the Sahara from Algiers to Nigeria, resulting in a powerfully simple work that sheds stale Western conventions to get at theater's universal truths.

name: Municipal Stadium
dealTitle: San Jose Broofest: "A Nightmare on Alma Street"
dealinfo: This Halloween, get freaky at Municipal Stadium with the San Jose Brew Fest, a monstrous mashup of craft beer and pulse-pounding fun. At "A Nightmare on Alma Street", you can enjoy three hours of unlimited craft beer samples from over 40 different breweries, feast on devilish dishes and show off your best scream at the photo booth. Make sure you come decked out in your coolest, most ghoulish, or sexiest Halloween get-up so you can compete in the costume contest. Plus, there'll be plenty of activities like bobbing for apples, hunting for hidden treats, decorating pumpkins and more. This beer-filled fright fest is brought to you by the masterminds behind nationwide foodie events like the Bacon and Beer Classic and the Lions Tigers and Brews.

name: Black Cat Licorice Theater
dealTitle: $6.00 for $12.00 - American Improv Theatre Players: Spontaneous Comedy, Instant Laughs
dealinfo: Improv is comedy without a net, where daredevil performers depend not only on the audience for suggestions, but also on their fellow performers for support and Lady Luck for inspiration. Done right, it's not just hilarious -- it's astonishing. The American Improv Theatre (AIT) Players do it right. Come laugh and marvel as the Players spin entire scenes from suggestions. The show begins with some silly, quick-moving improv games (Think  Whose Line Is It Anyway? ). Then the Players raise the stakes with longer, more connected scenes so good they seem scripted. But they're not: Everything that happens at Black Cat Licorice Theater is discovered in the moment.

name: Black Cat Licorice Theater
dealTitle: Stage 4 Improv Comedy: Making Up Broadway Musicals on the Spot, One Silly Song at a Time
dealinfo: Imagine if, with a simple suggestion, you could inspire a new Broadway musical in the heart of San Jose. That dream can at last come true at a Stage 4 Improv show, where the audience provides a prompt, and a foursome of funny dudes provides the laughs, inventing spontaneous scenes and songs on the spot, replete with wacky characters and loony plot lines. Lighting up the cozy confines of Black Cat Licorice Theater, this quartet of show tune showmen may be slightly off-key at times, but what they come up with still hits all the right notes.

name: Historic Hoover Theater
dealTitle: Traditional Flamenco "Juerga" (Jam Session) Featuring Fiery Music & Dance
dealinfo: The Flamenco Society of San Jose hosts this fiery flamenco jam session at the Historic Hoover Theatre. Known as "juergas," these jam sessions are flamenco festival staples that bring together dancers, singers and musicians -- all of them showcasing the passion and beauty of this centuries-old musical tradition. Performing at this juerga are dancer Koko de la Isla, singer Pirous de Caspio, guitarists Alberto Marques and Roberto Granados, and percussionist Ernesto Granados, along with a special performance by the Flamenco Society Dance Academy.

name: Winchester Mystery House
dealTitle: $17.00  for $26.00  - Winchester Mystery House: Tour 110 Rooms of a Victorian Architectural Marvel
dealinfo: A window built into the floor. Staircases leading to nowhere. Doors that open into blank walls. The Winchester Mansion is an architectural marvel like no other, full of unexplained mysteries and bizarre history. The 160-room mansion was built by Sarah Winchester, the widow of gun magnate William W. Winchester, in the late-1880s and was under continuous construction up until her death in 1922. The magnificent, maze-like home is shrouded in legends about its architectural oddities, including 47 fireplaces, 17 chimneys and countless dead ends. On this 65-minuted guided tour, you'll learn how Mrs. Winchester believed the house was haunted by those who'd been killed by her father-in-law's infamous Winchester Rifle, aka the Gun that Won the West. Your ticket also includes admission to the Victorian Gardens, the Historic Firearms Museum and the Specialty Gifts & Antique Products Museum.
